Revision history for Perl module Net::ACME

0.16 Mon Mar 11 2018
- No production changes.
- Formally discourage use of this module in light of Let’s Encrypt’s EOL
  announcement.
- Fix example module.
- Replace README.pod with README.md.

0.15
- Fix LICENSE file (again)

0.14
- Fix LICENSE file

0.13 Tue Jul 24 2018
- Fix indexing to make metacpan.org list this distribution again.
- Correct misinformation about pure-Perl-ness and XS/TLS dependency.

0.12 Mon Jan 15 2018
- Update docs to mention ACME v2.
- Fix LE get_terms_of_service().
- Use proper HTTP method names.
- Reorder this changelog in descending chronological order.
- Remove TLS-SNI authorization examples.
- Make this library easier to find in MetaCPAN search.

0.11 Wed Feb 08 2017
- Require bug-fixed Crypt::Perl version

0.1 Tue Jan 03 2017
- No more OpenSSL--we now go anywhere Perl goes!
- ECDSA support!
- Stronger warning about tls-sni-01 challenges. (Yowza, how’d that slip by??)

0.094 Thu Dec 22 2016
- Fixed MANIFEST (missing files broke tests)

0.093 Mon Dec 19 2016
- Remove Types::Serialiser dependency.

0.0922 Wed Nov 30 2016
- Trying once more to get a stable t/Net-ACME-HTTP.t
- Avoid clobbering $@ in Perl 5.10 and 5.8.

0.0921 Sun Nov 27 2016
- Still another test fix (grr, DNS)

0.092 Sun Nov 27 2016
- Remove vestigial Crypt::OpenSSL::RSA use()s in tests.
  (They were breaking some test runs.)

0.091 Fri Nov 25 2016
- Compatible with Perl 5.8+ (previously required 5.14+)
- Fix a clobber of $@
- Prevent clobber of $?
- Remove XS dependencies from tests.
- Add missing File::Slurp test dependency to Makefile.PL

0.09 Thu Nov 24 2016
- Finish porting cPanel tests
- Remove Class::Accessor dependency
- Add more documentation
- Need to test CPAN installation

0.03 Fri Nov 18 2016
- Fix broken Crypt::JWT dependency, make Crypt::OpenSSL::RSA optional
- Make http-01 challenge local handler create .well-known directory

0.02 Thu Nov 17 2016
- Remove CryptX dependency

0.01 Mon Nov 14 2016
- original port from cPanel
